ll* be needed, and prefered over druids/shamans, in exp groups.<br><br>However (one last thing to point out), if for some bizzare reason clerics do get less groups then they did before..... so what? *gasp* What is this blasphemy, clerics waiting more than 30 minutes lfg, an entire *hour* even?!? I personally have a 60 druid along with my monk, and there have been many.... many a day where Im lfg for a good 5 hours, without a single /tell, at which point I just have to log and not waste any more of my day. Now if this change does somehow change the demand for druids/shamans/clerics in exp (which I doubt it will), which in turn means more time for clerics lfg and less for the other priests, to that I say 'thank God'. I think this has been one of the better and more significant changes in caster balancing. (BTW I *fully* support raising the level of the spell from 54, in my opinion that is way too low for the spell).<br><br>     I apologize for ranting so much about a problem unrelated to monks, but having a druid I feel very strongly against this =(<br><br>EDIT: *hugs paragraphs* <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=solo>Solo</A> at: 8/21/02 12:39:36 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufatal67.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fatal67</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 384<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/21/02 2:32:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=253.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Please</span><hr size=1> I dont have an issue with other folks getting improved healing. I just find it strange they are giving it to the one class w