me and the entire game would be ruined as every cleric quit when Verant said they were considering giving shamans and druids chloroblast -- CHLOROBLAST fer crissake.  Yeesh.  I've never seen such hysteria, and it clearly turned out to be about pretty much nothing at all.<br><br>Shamans really could use another heal spell, though I think this might be a bit high for them because they can regen mana so well.  However, they are truly terrible healers in the high level game before they get torpor.  I can't tell you how many groups I ran extremely well at 59 and 60 without torpor, but that was with regrowth on both me and at least the main tank, and while wearing a fungi tunic to help my own mana regen.  But if hard-pressed against tough mobs to heal a main tank, I would be out of mana very quickly.  I REALLY needed regrowth and weak mobs, and sometimes plenty of time to canni, to heal high level players.  Chloroblast is the last heal shamans get before torpor(if they ever even get that one).  Lovely range and decent casting speed, but very low hitpoints healed.  Superior heal is not a satisfactory alternative.<br><br>As another priest class(yes, just like druid), shamans really need to be able to actually heal.  An improved heal of some sort would be great.  Honestly though, a 75% complete heal would be beyond most shaman's wildest dreams.<br><br>I suppose the only thing that could really balance it would be the lousy 10 second cast time.  Against really tough mobs, a heal every 10 seconds can give you plenty of time to die, and will effectively prevent doing canni to restore your mana very often at all.  It might even cause enough aggro to start chipping away at your health enough that you might be unable to canni or even just too chicken to try it.<br><br>I suppose there's some balance there then, but still it seems a bit like shamans hitting the lottery.<br><br>I really don't know what fizzle rate calculations mean IRL; wonder how much it really fizzles.<br><br>Oh, and Fatal67 -- I believe that most people put their money where their mouths are about how druids have no downsides by -- not playing them, and not grouping with them if they have a choice, either. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Like many if not most druids, I quit mine in the mid-50's because getting groups was too hard, even though I had plenty of friends and was well respected as a very good druid(I actually WAS one of those druids who knew how to control aggro and considered healing my first priority.)  And soloing -- please.  Much too boring, and the good loot is no more in soloing than the good times are.  My 60 shaman is 10x more fun to play and my 57 monk is probably just about as fun to play as my shaman or more.  And both of them died far less and, ahem, are EASIER to play.  (And both get MORE loot by a country mile.)<br><br>If you like druids that much, you like them better than most.  Including probably most people who started with them as their mains.<br><br>Don't wish a career as a druid on anyone please, unless you're willing to do it first. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sytharin>Sytharin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/21/02 7:58:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=253.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New 75% CH spells for Druid and Shaman are on Test!</span><hr size=1> There are a couple of things wrong with this change:<br><br>Let me state that my cleric is level 43, so I know nothing about the high end game for clerics so I am open to any and all correction.<br><br>The change should have never been made public until the cleric balancing was done, or at least after the changes to the cleric class being concidered were revealed.  This is a massive ego shot to clerics who, contrary to popular belief are in desprate need of an ego boost.   Clerics know that their usefullness in typical exp groups has gone down greatly.  The one and only thing that they have going for them is their ability to CH, thats it....there really isnt anything else that they can do that sets them apart or makes them feel powerful.  The ability to rez is a common argument, but I dont want to be invited into a group just because someone MIGHT die and need a rez.  Im not even talking high end here.  When you have to drag your warrior friend away from what he is doing so you can kill a blue mob for a quest that you want to complete, the feeling of power that you get from CH goes away quickly.  You realize that you are virtually useless without someone to heal.<br><br>Honestly, I can see why druids would be happy with the change as I hear they have very little to do on raids.  Shamans generally dont want this and seem to feel bad for clerics because of this change, they understand or at least can empathize with their plight.  Some people out there are actually complaining that the heal isnt powerful enough.<br><br>VI should have used its imagination and come up with another way to enhance druids in the high end.  Come up with something new, something not in the game currently.  Some new type of spell that does something that no one has seen before.  In other words...fresh.  Not to mention that they have taken the one spell that has really screwed up the balancing of this game, and made it more widespread.<br><br>What they have done is taken the one class that has only one great thing going for it (aside from rez), and given it to classes that have so many perks to them.  It stings.<br><br>VI better have something really great up thier sleeves for clerics in this round of balancing, its going to take a lot to make up for this.  Otherwise, you are going to see even less real clerics (read: not a bot) than you do now.<br><br>Of course, this is assuming the change goes live. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=205007>Sytharin</a><BR>Level 35 Iksar monk<BR>Bristlebane</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sytharin>Sytharin</A> at: 8/21/02 8:12:50 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufatal67.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fatal67</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 385<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/21/02 8:33:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=253.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New 75% CH spells for Druid and Shaman are on Test!</span><hr size=1> I love druids. I have to love druids. I have 15 of them in my guild. As a guild leader, i say hell yeah. Give me all the healers you can. As a player though, I think druids are still going to be lacking in the end game. Well, i guess you could start druid chain heal rotation.. god knows theres gonna be even more of them around.<br><br>Do something for the druids, make them have a role on the high end raids. Don't give them someone elses role.<br>Or give clerics dots and ports and sow..<br><br><br><br> <p><img src="http://amichi.not.net/~polyneices/Ramsus.gif"><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13934 target=_blank >Ramsus</a> </p><i></i></td><